{"parse":{"title":"Ezhuthu Kalari","pageid":44153979,"revid":729399992,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Ezhuthu Kalari</b>, a Malayalam term refers to the old traditional  village schools in Kerala.<sup id=\"cite_ref-The_Hindu_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-The_Hindu-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> These institutions were the major centers for initiating  elementary education. Most of the children in the past had to attend these centres for learning  <a href=\"/wiki/The_three_Rs\" title=\"The three Rs\">3Rs</a> .  It had been known by other names as well , such as  Ezhuthu pally  or Asan Kalari or <a href=\"/wiki/Pallikkoodam\" title=\"Pallikkoodam\">Pallikkoodam</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Ezhuthu Kalari were  believed to be evolved from the ancient  traditions of <a href=\"/wiki/Gurukula\" title=\"Gurukula\">Gurukula</a> system of schooling . Teachers  of these schools were addressed by the name  <a href=\"/wiki/Aasaan\" title=\"Aasaan\">Asan</a> or  <a href=\"/wiki/Thunchaththu_Ezhuthachan\" title=\"Thunchaththu Ezhuthachan\">Ezhuthu Asan</a>. <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ezhuthu_Kalari&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-The_Hindu-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-The_Hindu_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Raja, Dileep.G (2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2005/10/07/stories/2005100700420200.htm\">\"Of an old school of teachers\"</a>. Thiruvananthapuram: <i>The Hindu</i>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Of+an+old+school+of+teachers&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft.aulast=Raja&amp;rft.aufirst=Dileep.G&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fthehindu%2Ffr%2F2005%2F10%2F07%2Fstories%2F2005100700420200.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEzhuthu+Kalari\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Kerala District Gazetteers: Quilon ,Kerala (India),</i> A. Sreedhara Menon , page 423</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>People of India, Volume 27, Part 3 ,Anthropological Survey of India</i> Kumar Suresh Singh, page 1613</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/30px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/45px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a5/Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg/60px-Nuvola_apps_bookcase.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"128\" data-file-height=\"128\" /></a></td><td><i>This article relating to <a href=\"/wiki/Education\" title=\"Education\">education</a> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help Wikipedia by <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl